{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Zen Buddhism","audienceTags":["tradition:zen","tradition:buddhism","theme:mindfulness","theme:beginner-mind","audience:meditation"],"sortPriority":46,"groupingLevels":[],"groupingLabels":[],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Shunryu_Suzuki.json","supplementalDataPath":null,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Shunryu Suzuki","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"devotional","sourceId":"shunryuSuzuki","displayName":"Shunryu Suzuki","version":"1.0","language":"English","edition":"Wikiquote Verified","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","itemCount":20,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true},"data":[{"id":"suzuki-000001","text":"What is true zazen? What do you mean by Zen becomes Zen and you become you? You become you is a very important point. You become you. When you become you, even though you are in bed, you may not be you most of the time. Even though you are sitting here, I wonder whether you are you in its true sense. So to be you is zazen.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000002","text":"So it is not a matter of whether it is possible to attain Buddhahood, or if it is possible to make a tile a jewel. But just to work, just to live in this world with this understanding is the most important point, and that is our practice. That is true zazen.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000003","text":"The highest truth is daiji, translated as dai jiki in Chinese scriptures. This is the subject of the question the emperor asked Bodhidharma: \"What is the First Principle?\" Bodhidharma said, \"I don't know.\" \"I don't know\" is the First Principle.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000004","text":"Communication is — start by understanding — your own understanding about people. Even though you want them to understand you, you know, it is — unless you understand people, it is almost impossible. Don't you think so? Only when you understand people, they may understand you. So even though you do not say anything, if you understand people there is some communication.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000005","text":"When you do something, you should burn yourself completely, like a good bonfire, leaving no trace of yourself.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000006","text":"There are, strictly speaking, no enlightened people, there is only enlightened activity.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000007","text":"In the beginner's mind there are many possibilities, in the expert's there are few.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000008","text":"The true purpose of Zen is to see things as they are, to observe things as they are, and to let everything go as it goes. Zen practice is to open up our small mind.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000009","text":"You should rather be grateful for the weeds you have in your mind, because eventually they will enrich your practice.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000010","text":"Zazen practice is the direct expression of our true nature. Strictly speaking, for a human being, there is no other practice than this practice; there is no other way of life than this way of life.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000011","text":"If you take pride in your attainment or become discouraged because of your idealistic effort, your practice will confine you by a thick wall.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000012","text":"The purpose of studying Buddhism is not to study Buddhism but to study ourselves. You are not your body. You are the Big Activity. You are just expressing the smallest particle of the Big Activity. That is all. But when you become attached to a temporal expression of the Big Activity, it is time to talk about Buddhism.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000013","text":"The basic teaching of Buddhism is the teaching of transiency or change. That everything changes is the basic truth for each existence. No one can deny this truth and all teaching of Buddhism is condensed within it. This is the teaching for all of us. Wherever we go this teaching is true. This teaching is also understood as the teaching of selflessness. Because each existence is in constant change, there is no abiding self.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000014","text":"When we do not expect anything we can be ourselves. That is our way, to live fully in each moment of time.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000015","text":"It is a big mistake to think that the best way to express yourself is to do whatever you want, acting as you please. This is not expressing yourself. If you know what to do exactly, and you do it, then you can express yourself fully.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000016","text":"All descriptions of reality are limited expressions of the world of emptiness. Yet we attach to the descriptions and think they are reality. That is a mistake.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000017","text":"Instead of respecting things, we want to use them for ourselves and if it is difficult to use them, we want to conquer them.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000018","text":"Real Freedom is to not feel limited when wearing this Zen robe, this troublesome formal robe. Similarly, in our busy life we should wear this civilization without being bothered by it, without ignoring it, without being caught by it.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000019","text":"Nothing we see or hear is perfect. But right there in the imperfection is perfect reality.","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true},{"id":"suzuki-000020","text":"Crooked Cucumber: The Life and Teaching of Shunryu Suzuki","author":"Shunryu Suzuki","source":"Shunryu Suzuki","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beginner-mind","theme:mindfulness","theme:mindfulness,beginner-mind","tradition:buddhism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true}]}